The paper deals with the problem of estimating centrality scores of a target node in a graph while exploring only a sublinear number of nodes/arcs of the graph and performing a sublinear number of elementary operations. This problem is related to graph algorithms and graph mining, which are typically covered in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of computational and query complexity, which falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The techniques used in the paper involve probabilistic methods and approximation algorithms, which are relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of centrality measures such as PageRank and Heat Kernel, which are related to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
